Set Up Transaction Dispute Management

With Transaction Dispute Management, service agents can effortlessly and accurately capture customer disputes regarding their financial transactions with a guided intake form.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, and Unlimited Editions where Financial Services Cloud is enabled

Configure the Dispute Object
To associate the financial account of a customer with a dispute request, add a field to the Dispute object.

Assign Transaction Dispute Management Permissions to User
To use the dispute intake process, raise merchant alerts, initiate chargeback, and review second presentment, assign relevant permissions to your users.

Connect to MuleSoft and Enable Integration
To get financial transactions from a core banking system in the dispute intake form, connect your Salesforce and MuleSoft instances and enable integration between Salesforce and the core banking system.

Create an Integration Definition
Transaction Dispute Management uses fscserviceprocess.TransactionServiceIntegrationProvider integration definition. It calls the API to get the clientâ€™s financial transactions from the core banking system.

Customize the Page Layouts with Source System ID
Add the Source System ID field to the Financial Account and Account page layouts.

Add the Picklist Values Required for a Dispute Request
To indicate the type, subtype, and status of a dispute request, activate the picklist values.

Add Related Components
Associate the dispute intake OmniScript to an Action Launcher Deployment.
Activate the Transaction Dispute Service Process
Chargeback for Transaction Disputes
Einstein Generative AI to Compose and Send Emails for Transaction Dispute Requests
Dispute Intake OmniScript Components

Enable Merchant Alerts for Disputed Transactions
Transaction deflection helps you redirect the disputed transactions based on predefined business rules and criteria.

Set Up Deflection for Disputed Transactions
Enable User Access to User External Credentials Object

To use Transaction Dispute Management, follow these steps:

1. Configure the dispute object.
2. Assign relevant permissions to users.
3. Connect to MuleSoft and enable integration.
4. Create an integration definition.
5. Customize page layouts with source system ID.
6. Add picklist values for a dispute request.
7. Associate the dispute intake OmniScript to an action launcher deployment.
8. Activate the transaction dispute service process.
9. Enable merchant alerts for disputed transactions.
10. Set up deflection for disputed transactions.
11. Enable user access to user external credentials object.
